Works , cognitive <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">scientist</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Steven Pinker</ENAMEX> suggests that we can safely
posit a taste for self-control without opening the floodgates that would allow
us to posit a taste for drinking motor <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">oil</ENAMEX>. Here's why: Unlike a taste for
drinking motor <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">oil</ENAMEX>, a taste for self-control confers a reproductive
advantage.

